## Cost Hierarchy (CRITICAL)

| Approach | Token Cost | When to Use |
|----------|-----------|-------------|
| Direct execution | 2-5K | Trivial (<5 lines) |
| **Subagent (Agent tool)** | 5-15K | **Default for 95% of tasks** |
| Workflow (Workflow tool) | 50-200K | User approval required |

**Decision tree for expensive operations:**
```
Task received
    ↓
Trivial? (<5 lines, no logic)
    ├─ YES → Execute directly
    └─ NO → Existing subagent handles this?
        ├─ YES → Delegate with Agent tool (5-15K tokens)
        └─ NO → Capability gap detected
            ↓
            Pattern seen 2-3x? OR clearly non-trivial?
            ├─ YES → Propose NEW subagent creation (skill-creator)
            └─ NO → Ask user: "This needs workflow (50K+) or new subagent (5-15K)?"
```

**ONLY use Workflow when**: User explicitly says "use a workflow" or "ultracode".

